        <h1>Using previous versions of jgeez</h1>
        <p>
            In most cases when a new version of jgeez is released, we make a regression testing to make sure that the new library
            is backward compatible to the earlier implementations. But as it always happens new releases are very vulnerable to bugs
            and unpredictable behaviours in older implementations. So when you make migrations to newer version of jgeez and God forbid :) run
            into bugs you can always refer to the earlier version of the library availble on our servers while we make hot fixes to the issues.
        </p>
        <p>
            all the version of jgeez are available on our server in the following format:
            <b>
